            <fr:route>/forest/ualg-0002/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="algebra of a monad">algebra of a monad</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Given a <fr:link href="/forest/ualg-0001/" title="monad on a category" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/ualg-0001/" display-uri="ualg-0001" type="local">monad</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M : \mathcal {C} \to  \mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex>, an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>-<html:strong>algebra</html:strong> is defined as an object <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> equipped with a morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha  : MX \to  X]]></fr:tex>, such that the following two diagrams commute.
</html:p>
  <html:span class="tikz tikzcd">
    <fr:resource hash="ec3e2921a7219fd3435093d44a04c536"><fr:resource-content><html:img src="/forest/ec3e2921a7219fd3435093d44a04c536.svg" /></fr:resource-content><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[
            \usepackage{mlmodern, tikz, tikz-cd, quiver, mathtools, amssymb, stmaryrd, mathrsfs}
    ]]></fr:resource-source><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
      \begin {tikzcd}%tex
  {M^2X} & MX & X & MX \\
  MX & X && X
  \arrow["\alpha"', from=2-1, to=2-2]
  \arrow["\alpha", from=1-2, to=2-2]
  \arrow["\mu"', from=1-1, to=2-1]
  \arrow["M\alpha", from=1-1, to=1-2]
  \arrow["\operatorname{id}"', from=1-3, to=2-4]
  \arrow["\eta", from=1-3, to=1-4]
  \arrow["\alpha", from=1-4, to=2-4]\end {tikzcd}
    ]]></fr:resource-source></fr:resource>
  </html:span>
<html:p>
  In an unbiased formulation, we require the natural transformation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M^n \to  M]]></fr:tex> of the monad evaluated at the object <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> composed with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha  : MX \to  X]]></fr:tex> to be equal to <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[M^n X \xrightarrow {M^{n-1}\alpha } M^{n-1}X \to  \cdots  \xrightarrow {\alpha } X.]]></fr:tex></html:p><html:p>
  The algebras of a monad form a category <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}^M]]></fr:tex>, whose morphisms are commutative squares. This is also known as the <html:strong>Eilenberg–Moore category</html:strong>.
</html:p></fr:mainmatter>
